76void Caches::retrieveOriginFromDirectory(const String& folderPath, WorkQueue& queue, WTF::CompletionHandler<void(std::optional<WebCore::ClientOrigin>&&)>&& completionHandler)
77{
78 queue.dispatch([completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler), filename = cachesOriginFilename(folderPath)]() mutable {
79 if (!FileSystem::fileExists(filename)) {
80 RunLoop::main().dispatch([completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)]() mutable {
81 completionHandler(std::nullopt);
82 });
83 return;
84 }
85
86 auto channel = IOChannel::open(filename, IOChannel::Type::Read);
87 channel->read(0, std::numeric_limits<size_t>::max(), WorkQueue::main(), [completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)](const Data& data, int error) mutable {
88 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
89 if (error) {
90 RELEASE_LOG_ERROR(CacheStorage, "Caches::retrieveOriginFromDirectory failed reading channel with error %d", error);
91 completionHandler(std::nullopt);
92 return;
93 }
94 completionHandler(readOrigin(data));
95 });
96 });
97}
98
99void Caches::storeOrigin(CompletionCallback&& completionHandler)
100{
101 WTF::Persistence::Encoder encoder;
102 encoder << m_origin.topOrigin.protocol;
103 encoder << m_origin.topOrigin.host;
104 encoder << m_origin.topOrigin.port;
105 encoder << m_origin.clientOrigin.protocol;
106 encoder << m_origin.clientOrigin.host;
107 encoder << m_origin.clientOrigin.port;
108 m_engine->writeFile(cachesOriginFilename(m_rootPath), Data { encoder.buffer(), encoder.bufferSize() }, [protectedThis = makeRef(*this), completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)] (std::optional<Error>&& error) mutable {
109 completionHandler(WTFMove(error));
110 });
111}
112
113std::optional<WebCore::ClientOrigin> Caches::readOrigin(const Data& data)
114{
115 WTF::Persistence::Decoder decoder(data.data(), data.size());
116
117 std::optional<WebCore::SecurityOriginData> topOrigin;
118 decoder >> topOrigin;
119 if (!topOrigin)
120 return std::nullopt;
121
122 std::optional<WebCore::SecurityOriginData> clientOrigin;
123 decoder >> clientOrigin;
124 if (!clientOrigin)
125 return std::nullopt;
126
127 return {{
128 WTFMove(*topOrigin),
129 WTFMove(*clientOrigin)
130 }};
131}
132
133void Caches::initialize(WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::CompletionCallback&& callback)
134{
135 if (m_isInitialized) {
136 callback(std::nullopt);
137 return;
138 }
139
140 if (m_rootPath.isNull()) {
141 makeDirty();
142 m_isInitialized = true;
143 callback(std::nullopt);
144 return;
145 }
146
147 if (m_storage) {
148 m_pendingInitializationCallbacks.append(WTFMove(callback));
149 return;
150 }
151
152 size_t capacity = std::numeric_limits<size_t>::max(); // We use a per-origin quota instead of a global capacity.
153 auto storage = Storage::open(m_rootPath, Storage::Mode::AvoidRandomness, capacity);
154 if (!storage) {
155 RELEASE_LOG_ERROR(CacheStorage, "Caches::initialize failed opening storage");
156 callback(Error::WriteDisk);
157 return;
158 }
159
160 m_pendingInitializationCallbacks.append(WTFMove(callback));
161 m_storage = storage.releaseNonNull();
162 m_storage->writeWithoutWaiting();
163
164 storeOrigin([this] (std::optional<Error>&& error) mutable {
165 if (error) {
166 RELEASE_LOG_ERROR(CacheStorage, "Caches::initialize failed storing origin with error %d", static_cast<int>(*error));
167
168 auto pendingCallbacks = WTFMove(m_pendingInitializationCallbacks);
169 for (auto& callback : pendingCallbacks)
170 callback(Error::WriteDisk);
171
172 m_storage = nullptr;
173 return;
174 }
175
176 readCachesFromDisk([this](Expected<Vector<Cache>, Error>&& result) mutable {
177 makeDirty();
178
179 if (!result.has_value()) {
180 RELEASE_LOG_ERROR(CacheStorage, "Caches::initialize failed reading caches from disk with error %d", static_cast<int>(result.error()));
181
182 auto pendingCallbacks = WTFMove(m_pendingInitializationCallbacks);
183 for (auto& callback : pendingCallbacks)
184 callback(result.error());
185
186 m_storage = nullptr;
187 return;
188 }
189 m_caches = WTFMove(result.value());
190
191 initializeSize();
192 });
193 });
194}
195
196void Caches::updateSizeFile(CompletionHandler<void()>&& completionHandler)
197{
198 if (!m_engine) {
199 completionHandler();
200 return;
201 }
202
203 m_engine->writeSizeFile(cachesSizeFilename(m_rootPath), m_size, WTFMove(completionHandler));
204}
205
206void Caches::initializeSize()
207{
208 if (!m_storage) {
209 auto pendingCallbacks = WTFMove(m_pendingInitializationCallbacks);
210 for (auto& callback : pendingCallbacks)
211 callback(Error::Internal);
212 return;
213 }
214
215 uint64_t size = 0;
216 m_storage->traverse({ }, { }, [protectedThis = makeRef(*this), this, protectedStorage = makeRef(*m_storage), size](const auto* storage, const auto& information) mutable {
217 if (!storage) {
218 if (m_pendingInitializationCallbacks.isEmpty()) {
219 // Caches was cleared so let's not get initialized.
220 m_storage = nullptr;
221 return;
222 }
223 m_size = size;
224 updateSizeFile([this, protectedThis = WTFMove(protectedThis)]() mutable {
225 m_isInitialized = true;
226 auto pendingCallbacks = WTFMove(m_pendingInitializationCallbacks);
227 for (auto& callback : pendingCallbacks)
228 callback(std::nullopt);
229 });
230 return;
231 }
232 auto decoded = Cache::decodeRecordHeader(*storage);
233 if (decoded)
234 size += decoded->size;
235 });
236}

238void Caches::detach()
239{
240 m_engine = nullptr;
241 m_rootPath = { };
242 clearPendingWritingCachesToDiskCallbacks();
243}
244
245void Caches::clear(CompletionHandler<void()>&& completionHandler)
246{
247 if (m_isWritingCachesToDisk) {
248 m_pendingWritingCachesToDiskCallbacks.append([this, completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)] (auto&& error) mutable {
249 this->clear(WTFMove(completionHandler));
250 });
251 return;
252 }
253
254 auto pendingCallbacks = WTFMove(m_pendingInitializationCallbacks);
255 for (auto& callback : pendingCallbacks)
256 callback(Error::Internal);
257
258 if (m_engine)
259 m_engine->removeFile(cachesListFilename(m_rootPath));
260 if (m_storage) {
261 m_storage->clear(String { }, -WallTime::infinity(), [protectedThis = makeRef(*this), completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)]() mutable {
262 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
263 protectedThis->clearMemoryRepresentation();
264 completionHandler();
265 });
266 return;
267 }
268 clearMemoryRepresentation();
269 clearPendingWritingCachesToDiskCallbacks();
270 completionHandler();
271}
272
273void Caches::clearPendingWritingCachesToDiskCallbacks()
274{
275 auto pendingWritingCachesToDiskCallbacks = WTFMove(m_pendingWritingCachesToDiskCallbacks);
276 for (auto& callback : pendingWritingCachesToDiskCallbacks)
277 callback(Error::Internal);
278}

280Cache* Caches::find(const String& name)
281{
282 auto position = m_caches.findMatching([&](const auto& item) { return item.name() == name; });
283 return (position != notFound) ? &m_caches[position] : nullptr;
284}
285
286Cache* Caches::find(uint64_t identifier)
287{
288 auto position = m_caches.findMatching([&](const auto& item) { return item.identifier() == identifier; });
289 if (position != notFound)
290 return &m_caches[position];
291
292 position = m_removedCaches.findMatching([&](const auto& item) { return item.identifier() == identifier; });
293 return (position != notFound) ? &m_removedCaches[position] : nullptr;
294}
295
296void Caches::open(const String& name, CacheIdentifierCallback&& callback)
297{
298 ASSERT(m_isInitialized);
299 ASSERT(m_engine);
300
301 if (m_isWritingCachesToDisk) {
302 m_pendingWritingCachesToDiskCallbacks.append([this, name, callback = WTFMove(callback)] (auto&& error) mutable {
303 if (error) {
304 callback(makeUnexpected(error.value()));
305 return;
306 }
307 this->open(name, WTFMove(callback));
308 });
309 return;
310 }
311
312 if (auto* cache = find(name)) {
313 cache->open([cacheIdentifier = cache->identifier(), callback = WTFMove(callback)](std::optional<Error>&& error) mutable {
314 if (error) {
315 callback(makeUnexpected(error.value()));
316 return;
317 }
318 callback(CacheIdentifierOperationResult { cacheIdentifier, false });
319 });
320 return;
321 }
322
323 makeDirty();
324
325 uint64_t cacheIdentifier = m_engine->nextCacheIdentifier();
326 m_caches.append(Cache { *this, cacheIdentifier, Cache::State::Open, String { name }, createCanonicalUUIDString() });
327
328 writeCachesToDisk([callback = WTFMove(callback), cacheIdentifier](std::optional<Error>&& error) mutable {
329 callback(CacheIdentifierOperationResult { cacheIdentifier, !!error });
330 });
331}
332
333void Caches::remove(uint64_t identifier, CacheIdentifierCallback&& callback)
334{
335 ASSERT(m_isInitialized);
336 ASSERT(m_engine);
337
338 if (m_isWritingCachesToDisk) {
339 m_pendingWritingCachesToDiskCallbacks.append([this, identifier, callback = WTFMove(callback)] (auto&& error) mutable {
340 if (error) {
341 callback(makeUnexpected(error.value()));
342 return;
343 }
344 this->remove(identifier, WTFMove(callback));
345 });
346 return;
347 }
348
349 auto position = m_caches.findMatching([&](const auto& item) { return item.identifier() == identifier; });
350
351 if (position == notFound) {
352 ASSERT(m_removedCaches.findMatching([&](const auto& item) { return item.identifier() == identifier; }) != notFound);
353 callback(CacheIdentifierOperationResult { 0, false });
354 return;
355 }
356
357 makeDirty();
358
359 m_removedCaches.append(WTFMove(m_caches[position]));
360 m_caches.remove(position);
361
362 writeCachesToDisk([callback = WTFMove(callback), identifier](std::optional<Error>&& error) mutable {
363 callback(CacheIdentifierOperationResult { identifier, !!error });
364 });
365}
366
367bool Caches::hasActiveCache() const
368{
369 if (m_removedCaches.size())
370 return true;
371 return m_caches.findMatching([](const auto& item) { return item.isActive(); }) != notFound;
372}
373
374void Caches::dispose(Cache& cache)
375{
376 auto position = m_removedCaches.findMatching([&](const auto& item) { return item.identifier() == cache.identifier(); });
377 if (position != notFound) {
378 if (m_storage)
379 m_storage->remove(cache.keys(), [] { });
380
381 m_removedCaches.remove(position);
382 return;
383 }
384 ASSERT(m_caches.findMatching([&](const auto& item) { return item.identifier() == cache.identifier(); }) != notFound);
385
386 // We cannot clear the memory representation in ephemeral sessions since we would loose all data.
387 if (!shouldPersist())
388 return;
389
390 cache.clearMemoryRepresentation();
391
392 if (!hasActiveCache())
393 clearMemoryRepresentation();
394}
395
396static inline Data encodeCacheNames(const Vector<Cache>& caches)
397{
398 WTF::Persistence::Encoder encoder;
399
400 uint64_t size = caches.size();
401 encoder << size;
402 for (auto& cache : caches) {
403 encoder << cache.name();
404 encoder << cache.uniqueName();
405 }
406
407 return Data { encoder.buffer(), encoder.bufferSize() };
408}
409
410static inline Expected<Vector<std::pair<String, String>>, Error> decodeCachesNames(const Data& data)
411{
412 WTF::Persistence::Decoder decoder(data.data(), data.size());
413 std::optional<uint64_t> count;
414 decoder >> count;
415 if (!count)
416 return makeUnexpected(Error::ReadDisk);
417
418 Vector<std::pair<String, String>> names;
419 if (!names.tryReserveCapacity(*count))
420 return makeUnexpected(Error::ReadDisk);
421
422 for (size_t index = 0; index < *count; ++index) {
423 std::optional<String> name;
424 decoder >> name;
425 if (!name)
426 return makeUnexpected(Error::ReadDisk);
427 std::optional<String> uniqueName;
428 decoder >> uniqueName;
429 if (!uniqueName)
430 return makeUnexpected(Error::ReadDisk);
431
432 names.uncheckedAppend({ WTFMove(*name), WTFMove(*uniqueName) });
433 }
434 return names;
435}
436
437void Caches::readCachesFromDisk(WTF::Function<void(Expected<Vector<Cache>, Error>&&)>&& callback)
438{
439 ASSERT(m_engine);
440 ASSERT(!m_isInitialized);
441 ASSERT(m_caches.isEmpty());
442
443 if (!shouldPersist()) {
444 callback(Vector<Cache> { });
445 return;
446 }
447
448 auto filename = cachesListFilename(m_rootPath);
449 if (!FileSystem::fileExists(filename)) {
450 callback(Vector<Cache> { });
451 return;
452 }
453
454 m_engine->readFile(filename, [protectedThis = makeRef(*this), this, callback = WTFMove(callback)](const Data& data, int error) mutable {
455 if (!m_engine) {
456 callback(Vector<Cache> { });
457 return;
458 }
459
460 if (error) {
461 RELEASE_LOG_ERROR(CacheStorage, "Caches::readCachesFromDisk failed reading caches from disk with error %d", error);
462 callback(makeUnexpected(Error::ReadDisk));
463 return;
464 }
465
466 auto result = decodeCachesNames(data);
467 if (!result.has_value()) {
468 RELEASE_LOG_ERROR(CacheStorage, "Caches::decodeCachesNames failed decoding caches with error %d", static_cast<int>(result.error()));
469 callback(makeUnexpected(result.error()));
470 return;
471 }
472 callback(WTF::map(WTFMove(result.value()), [this] (auto&& pair) {
473 return Cache { *this, m_engine->nextCacheIdentifier(), Cache::State::Uninitialized, WTFMove(pair.first), WTFMove(pair.second) };
474 }));
475 });
476}
477
478void Caches::writeCachesToDisk(CompletionCallback&& callback)
479{
480 ASSERT(!m_isWritingCachesToDisk);
481 ASSERT(m_isInitialized);
482 if (!shouldPersist()) {
483 callback(std::nullopt);
484 return;
485 }
486
487 ASSERT(m_engine);
488
489 if (m_caches.isEmpty()) {
490 m_engine->removeFile(cachesListFilename(m_rootPath));
491 callback(std::nullopt);
492 return;
493 }
494
495 m_isWritingCachesToDisk = true;
496 m_engine->writeFile(cachesListFilename(m_rootPath), encodeCacheNames(m_caches), [this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), callback = WTFMove(callback)](std::optional<Error>&& error) mutable {
497 m_isWritingCachesToDisk = false;
498 if (error)
499 RELEASE_LOG_ERROR(CacheStorage, "Caches::writeCachesToDisk failed writing caches to disk with error %d", static_cast<int>(*error));
500
501 callback(WTFMove(error));
502 while (!m_pendingWritingCachesToDiskCallbacks.isEmpty() && !m_isWritingCachesToDisk)
503 m_pendingWritingCachesToDiskCallbacks.takeFirst()(std::nullopt);
504 });
505}

507void Caches::readRecordsList(Cache& cache, NetworkCache::Storage::TraverseHandler&& callback)
508{
509 ASSERT(m_isInitialized);
510
511 if (!m_storage) {
512 callback(nullptr, { });
513 return;
514 }
515 m_storage->traverse(cache.uniqueName(), { }, [protectedStorage = makeRef(*m_storage), callback = WTFMove(callback)](const auto* storage, const auto& information) {
516 callback(storage, information);
517 });
518}

520void Caches::requestSpace(uint64_t spaceRequired, WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::CompletionCallback&& callback)
521{
522 if (!m_engine) {
523 callback(Error::QuotaExceeded);
524 return;
525 }
526
527 m_engine->requestSpace(m_origin, spaceRequired, [callback = WTFMove(callback)](auto decision) mutable {
528 switch (decision) {
529 case WebCore::StorageQuotaManager::Decision::Deny:
530 callback(Error::QuotaExceeded);
531 return;
532 case WebCore::StorageQuotaManager::Decision::Grant:
533 callback({ });
534 };
535 });
536}
537
538void Caches::writeRecord(const Cache& cache, const RecordInformation& recordInformation, Record&& record, uint64_t previousRecordSize, CompletionCallback&& callback)
539{
540 ASSERT(m_isInitialized);
541
542 ASSERT(m_size >= previousRecordSize);
543 m_size += recordInformation.size;
544 m_size -= previousRecordSize;
545
546 if (!shouldPersist()) {
547 m_volatileStorage.set(recordInformation.key, makeUnique<Record>(WTFMove(record)));
548 callback(std::nullopt);
549 return;
550 }
551
552 m_storage->store(Cache::encode(recordInformation, record), { }, [this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), protectedStorage = makeRef(*m_storage), callback = WTFMove(callback)](int error) mutable {
553 if (error) {
554 RELEASE_LOG_ERROR(CacheStorage, "Caches::writeRecord failed with error %d", error);
555 callback(Error::WriteDisk);
556 return;
557 }
558 updateSizeFile([callback = WTFMove(callback)]() mutable {
559 callback(std::nullopt);
560 });
561 });
562}
563
564void Caches::readRecord(const NetworkCache::Key& key, WTF::Function<void(Expected<Record, Error>&&)>&& callback)
565{
566 ASSERT(m_isInitialized);
567
568 if (!shouldPersist()) {
569 if (auto* record = m_volatileStorage.get(key))
570 return callback(record->copy());
571 return callback(makeUnexpected(Error::Internal));
572 }
573
574 m_storage->retrieve(key, 4, [protectedStorage = makeRef(*m_storage), callback = WTFMove(callback)](std::unique_ptr<Storage::Record> storage, const Storage::Timings&) mutable {
575 if (!storage) {
576 RELEASE_LOG_ERROR(CacheStorage, "Caches::readRecord failed reading record from disk");
577 callback(makeUnexpected(Error::ReadDisk));
578 return false;
579 }
580
581 auto record = Cache::decode(*storage);
582 if (!record) {
583 RELEASE_LOG_ERROR(CacheStorage, "Caches::readRecord failed decoding record from disk");
584 callback(makeUnexpected(Error::ReadDisk));
585 return false;
586 }
587
588 callback(WTFMove(record.value()));
589 return true;
590 });
591}
592
593void Caches::removeRecord(const RecordInformation& record)
594{
595 ASSERT(m_isInitialized);
596
597 ASSERT(m_size >= record.size);
598 m_size -= record.size;
599 updateSizeFile([] { });
600
601 removeCacheEntry(record.key);
602}
603
604void Caches::removeCacheEntry(const NetworkCache::Key& key)
605{
606 ASSERT(m_isInitialized);
607
608 if (!shouldPersist()) {
609 m_volatileStorage.remove(key);
610 return;
611 }
612 if (m_storage)
613 m_storage->remove(key);
614}
615
616void Caches::clearMemoryRepresentation()
617{
618 makeDirty();
619 m_caches.clear();
620 m_isInitialized = false;
621
622 // Clear storages as a memory optimization.
623 m_storage = nullptr;
624 m_volatileStorage.clear();
625}
626
627bool Caches::isDirty(uint64_t updateCounter) const
628{
629 ASSERT(m_updateCounter >= updateCounter);
630 return m_updateCounter != updateCounter;
631}
632
633const NetworkCache::Salt& Caches::salt() const
634{
635 if (m_engine)
636 return m_engine->salt();
637
638 if (!m_volatileSalt)
639 m_volatileSalt = Salt { };
640
641 return m_volatileSalt.value();
642}
643
644void Caches::cacheInfos(uint64_t updateCounter, CacheInfosCallback&& callback)
645{
646 if (m_isWritingCachesToDisk) {
647 m_pendingWritingCachesToDiskCallbacks.append([this, updateCounter, callback = WTFMove(callback)] (auto&& error) mutable {
648 if (error) {
649 callback(makeUnexpected(error.value()));
650 return;
651 }
652 this->cacheInfos(updateCounter, WTFMove(callback));
653 });
654 return;
655 }
656
657 Vector<CacheInfo> cacheInfos;
658 if (isDirty(updateCounter)) {
659 cacheInfos.reserveInitialCapacity(m_caches.size());
660 for (auto& cache : m_caches)
661 cacheInfos.uncheckedAppend(CacheInfo { cache.identifier(), cache.name() });
662 }
663 callback(CacheInfos { WTFMove(cacheInfos), m_updateCounter });
664}
665
666void Caches::appendRepresentation(StringBuilder& builder) const
667{
668 ASSERT(m_pendingInitializationCallbacks.isEmpty());
669 ASSERT(m_pendingWritingCachesToDiskCallbacks.isEmpty());
670
671 builder.append("{ \"persistent\": [");
672
673 bool isFirst = true;
674 for (auto& cache : m_caches) {
675 ASSERT(!cache.hasPendingOpeningCallbacks());
676 if (!isFirst)
677 builder.append(", ");
678 isFirst = false;
679 builder.append("\"");
680 builder.append(cache.name());
681 builder.append("\"");
682 }
683
684 builder.append("], \"removed\": [");
685
686 isFirst = true;
687 for (auto& cache : m_removedCaches) {
688 if (!isFirst)
689 builder.append(", ");
690 isFirst = false;
691 builder.append("\"");
692 builder.append(cache.name());
693 builder.append("\"");
694 }
695 builder.append("]}\n");
696}
697
698uint64_t Caches::storageSize() const
699{
700 ASSERT(m_isInitialized);
701 if (!shouldPersist())
702 return 0;
703 return m_storage->approximateSize();
704}
